<section id="process" class="process">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">How I Work</p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-head" style="border:none; margin-bottom:0; padding-bottom:0;">
      <h2>From Brief To Final Art</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="wrap" style="margin-top:64px;">
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-label">Brief</div>
        <h4>Understand the goal</h4>
        <p>Before opening any tool, I clarify what the piece needs to achieve — awareness, conversion, internal buy-in — the same way I used to scope a QA improvement project.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-label">Concept</div>
        <h4>Sketch directions</h4>
        <p>Rough layout and mood options, explored fast, so the client is choosing a direction early instead of reacting to a finished piece.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-label">Build</div>
        <h4>Produce the final art</h4>
        <p>Full production in Photoshop, Illustrator, or Canva — manipulation, retouching, and layout work refined through rounds of self-review.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-label">Consultation</div>
        <h4>Review every detail together</h4>
        <p>We go through colors, typography, and layout side by side — checking for anything missing or off-brand. Nothing moves to final files until you've signed off.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-label">Deliver</div>
        <h4>Ship it ready to use</h4>
        <p>Once there are no further changes, final copy is delivered — export-ready and sized correctly for the actual placement, with no late surprises.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


